race.comment: ROCKIN' ROBIN (5) set the tempo last start at Northam when only caught late, finishing 0.9L off the winner. He was only third-up there off one trial, so it's easy to think there's still some improvement to come. Can roll across once again, dictate the tempo, and land the knockout blow. MISS GRAPHENE (8) missed narrowly at Northam two back before running into a dominant winner over 1800m at Ascot last time out. She's likely to get back from the draw again, but she was closing strongly last time out. Watch for her late in the race. HARRIS ROAD (6) is a lightly raced gelding who has shown glimpses in his past couple. He wasn't far behind ROCKIN' ROBIN last start at Northam and he can follow that runner across from the sticky gate. Expecting another bold run. MACHO ARQUERO (2) steps out in trip today and can be finishing strongly.
